args:
A few days prior to the clash between the
prince's forces and the alliance led by Chelle
and Leonidas, Phares makes his way to a cell
in the bowels of the royal palace. With the truth
in hand, he seeks to release an individual
termed ＂the darkest secret of the royal family.＂
A few days prior to the clash between the prince's\nNew Alberian Army and the Dyrenell Army led by\nLeonidas and Chelle...
Have there been any developments since\nI last came to call here?
None, Highness. In fact, I've heard nary\na peep in there since your last visit.
Er, but if it please Your Highness,\nwhat exactly is IN that room?
It does not please.\nOne of your station has no\nneed for such information.

O-of course, sire! It's just that... Well,
all of this secrecy and not-knowing and
so on has me near to taking leave of
my wits, so it does.
I mean, a man can only stand in a dank\nbasement keeping watch over Ilia-knows-\nwhat for so long.
Does your curiosity truly burn so?\nVery well. You may join me inside.
Of course. I have a particular respect\nfor those with curious hearts.
Such measures hardly seem necessary.\nMy older brother wears his cowardice\nwith unexpected openness.
Regardless, I was ordered to be doubly\nsure of all security arrangements, sire.
Let me just open this last door...
And now, my friend, feast your eyes.\nLook and drink deep upon the greatest\nshame of the Alberian royal family.
In a sense. To be more precise, he is being\nrobbed of consciousness by an extremely\npowerful magic.
That must be what the binding is for.\nI must say, it is a disturbing sight...

Said binding is called a witchhasp.
It was custom-crafted by the greatest
practitioners in the land, each of whom
poured their full measure of power into it.
...Yes. It is time to be gone from here.
Understood, Your Highness.\nLet us make our way back.
*sigh* I thank you for this, Your Highness.\nAnd I swear upon my honor that not a\nword of it will pass my lips.
Feel free to observe further, my good man.\nLook upon him as long as you like until\nyour heart and mind have been quieted.
Er, but did you not say it was time\nto be going just a moment ago?
I was not speaking to you, but to him.
As I said, it is time.
Blast! This bodes ill! If we're not quick\nto inform the palace, then—
Such warnings are unnecessary.\nHe has already been released.
A curious heart sated as it thrums its\nlast beat is a satisfying end for any man.\nNow then...

Those lacking in wisdom have termed him
＂the darkest secret of the royal family.＂
I, however, believe he is not a secret,
but a POSSIBILITY.
Power ought not be feared! Rather,\nit should be studied and harnessed.
My apologies for keeping you waiting.\nTell me, how does it feel to be awakened?
It is not disagreeable at all...my brother.
